    comment: '<p>Mainly useful for prototyping, there are multiple ways to interact with the user.</p>\n<pre><code>prompt(text,default)\n</code></pre>\n<p>This outputs a modal window with the text, <code>OK</code>/<code>CANCEL</code> buttons and input field.</p>\n<pre><code>alert(message):\n</code></pre>\n<p>This outputs a window with the message and stops execution until the visitor presses the “OK” button.</p>\n<pre><code>confirm(message):\n</code></pre>\n<p>This outputs the message with two buttons: <code>OK</code> and <code>CANCEL</code>.</p>\n<p>Always set the default value in prompt, otherwise browsers may insert "undefined" into the dialog.</p>\n',
